MBOMBELA –    According to the department of Safety and Security spokesman Joseph Mabuza,  it is alleged that one of the was attempting to overtake the other when the accident took place. “Two males and two females including the driver were killed.” A secondary collision happened on the same road involving two sedans. ” One person was  slightly  injured,  another person was stabilised at the scene and transported to Themba Hospital. He said  a case of culpable homicide and drunken driving was registered with SAPS White River.